  "text": "The existence of the surface polygons seems connected with the fact that the flow is turbulent. In fact, switching transitions are observed in similar but smaller systems, where the flow irregularly switches between a weakly deformed, rotationally symmetric state and a strongly deformed state with two corners. Here, the free surface touches the bottom, and this transition is linked with a transition to turbulence [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Thus the strong mixing present in the turbulent flow seems to be necessary for the formation of surface polygons.",
